<h3>Possible cases</h3>
<h4> Close bug using version</h4>
You close the bug with a quick note to the reporter.
<p>
<pre>
To: XXXXXX-done@bugs.debian.org
Subject: Bug fixed

Version: Y.Y-Y

Hi!

The bug you reported has been fixed in KDE Y.Y-Y

Cheers.
</pre>
</p>


<h4> Bug forwarded in the KDE bugzilla</h4>
You send a control email to mark the bug as forwarded so bts-link learns about it.

<p>
<pre>
To: control@bugs.debian.org
Subject: bug forwarding

forwarded XXXXXX https://bugs.kde.org/show_bug.cgi?id=nnnnnn
thanks
</pre>
</p>


<h4> Bug forwarded thas has been *fixed* in the KDE bugzilla</h4>

<p>
Check if it is really fixed for you, and if it is. Then you are in the case "Close the bug using version".
</p>


<h4> Bug is present in newer version</h4>

<p>
<pre>
To: control@bugs.debian.org
Subject: bug found in new version

found XXXXXX Y.Y-Y
thanks
</pre>
</p>
